description: List the multi-region endpoints (global-endpoints). Only multi-region endpoints (global-endpoints) whose primary region is the AWS-Region where operation is executed will be listed.

nested_items.name: MultiRegionEndpoints
nested_items.description: An array that contains key multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint) properties.

nested_items.name: EndpointName
nested_items.description: The name of the multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint).

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint).
CREATING --- The resource is being provisioned.
READY --- The resource is ready to use.
FAILED --- The resource failed to be provisioned.
DELETING --- The resource is being deleted as requested.

nested_items.name: EndpointId
nested_items.description: The ID of the multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint).

nested_items.name: Regions
nested_items.description: Primary and secondary regions between which multi-region endpoint splits sending traffic.

nested_items.name: CreatedTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time stamp of when the multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint) was created.

nested_items.name: LastUpdatedTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time stamp of when the multi-region endpoint (global-endpoint) was last updated.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: A token indicating that there are additional multi-region endpoints (global-endpoints) available to be listed. Pass this token to a subsequent ListMultiRegionEndpoints call to retrieve the next page.
